rComments: A very good professor. His English is also very good, he understands databases inside out. Would definitely recommend his course. Most useful CS course I've taken so far.
He is generally a good prof but I hope he speaks English. Although It is not a problem for me that he speaks Greek in class since I'm also from Greece. However, I believe most of the students aren't.

Although his voice can be hard to understand, his slides (always posted online) are among the most informative I've seen, and he responds VERY quickly on the discussion board (his written English is a LOT better than his spoken English :P). Recommend taking his course, but skip lectures and self-study + get his help on the discussion board.

He is generally a good prof but I hope he speaks English. Although It is not a problem for me that he speaks Greek in class since my name is Papastathoupolous, which means I'm also from Greece. However, I believe most of the students aren't.
Helpful, willing to explain, responds both online and in person quickly, Slides cover everything.

Slides are excellent so you'll never fall behind, even if you miss lectures. Assignments and tests are reasonable and he usually responds promptly and helpfully on the discussion board. If you're having a hard time in his course, you need to practice!
